{"TopicId":142571,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"1.1.3 - wheels inop? what gives?","CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T01:45:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T01:45:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/4Z5DQmr.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00224Z5DQmr.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbo Jangles","CreatedById":165798,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T02:27:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi Xyphos!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s tough to see in the screenshot, but it looks like you didn\u0027t rotate the wheel to face the proper direction in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. They need to be rotated 90 degrees I believe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you rotated properly during design, then it could be from clipping the wheels into other parts with the offset tool. I have seen many posts regarding this issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Jimbo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Due to my status as a forum noob, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142469-grenartia/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022142469\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/142469-grenartia/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Grenartia\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0beat me to the punch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-27T02:58:57Z\u0022 title=\u002206/27/2016 02:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jimbo Jangles\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Grenartia","CreatedById":142469,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T02:49:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like your wheels are too close to other parts. That\u0027s been a problem even in 1.1.2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iamsodarncool","CreatedById":138967,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T03:20:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Wheel blocked: Yes\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T03:32:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAW MAN,\u00A0 what a PITA.\u003Cbr\u003E\nokay, thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T06:25:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222649219\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022142571\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466998340\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139010\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xyphos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Xyphos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAW MAN,\u00A0 what a PITA.\u003Cbr\u003E\nokay, thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis will be fixed in 1.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T11:49:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes -- for now, don\u0027t use the \u0022Move\u0022 tool to offset wheels so that they are extra close to each other, or to other parts, or they won\u0027t work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-27T14:48:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re making a truck that can fit in a Mk3 cargo bay - it\u0027s going to take a lot of careful adjustments that can get ruined each time you gizmo something without deactivating the angle snap first. \u00A0It\u0027s hard to see where the wheels invisibly collide with something else, but that\u0027s what the game believes is happening. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re just making a rover, then space the wheels way out to the sides and it\u0027ll be fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}